    "cooking_instructions": [
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Boil a kettle</p><p>Add your <strong>egg[s]</strong> to a pot of <strong>boiled water </strong>with a pinch of <strong>salt</strong> and bring to the boil over a high heat (salt prevents the eggs from cracking)</p><p>Once boiling, cook for exactly 8 min for perfect, mid-boiled eggs, then fill a bowl of <strong>very cold water </strong>and add the <strong>cooked egg[s] </strong>to the bowl and set aside</p>",
            "order": 1,
            "image": "/images/instructions/kerala-egg-curry-with-coriander-rice-and-poppadoms/step-1.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Heat a large, wide-based pan (preferably non-stick) over a medium-high heat with a knob of <strong>butter</strong></p><p>Once melted, add your<strong> yellow</strong> <strong>mustard seeds </strong>and <strong>half </strong>of your <strong>garam masala</strong> (you'll use the rest later!)</p><p>Cook for 2-3 min or until fragrant then set aside and reserve the pan \u2013 this is your <strong>masala mustard butter</strong></p>",
            "order": 2,
            "image": "/images/instructions/kerala-egg-curry-with-coriander-rice-and-poppadoms/step-2.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Reboil half a kettle</p><p>Peel and finely slice your<strong> red onion[s]</strong></p><p>Chop your <strong>tomato[es] </strong>into wedges</p><p>Chop your <strong>coriander</strong> finely, including the stalks</p><p>Crush your <strong>cardamom pods</strong> open by squashing them with the side of a knife</p>",
            "order": 3,
            "image": "/images/instructions/kerala-egg-curry-with-coriander-rice-and-poppadoms/step-3.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Return the reserved pan to a medium-high heat with a drizzle of <strong>vegetable oil</strong></p><p>Once hot, add the <strong>sliced onion </strong>and the <strong>tomato wedges </strong>and cook for 5-6 min or until starting to soften</p>",
            "order": 4,
            "image": "/images/instructions/kerala-egg-curry-with-coriander-rice-and-poppadoms/step-4.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Add your <strong>basmati rice</strong> and 300ml<span class=\"text-purple\"> [390ml]</span> <span class=\"text-danger\">[600ml]</span> <strong>cold water</strong> to a pot with a lid and bring to the boil over a high heat</p><p>Once boiling, reduce the heat to very low and cook, covered, for 10-12 min or until all the water has absorbed and the rice is cooked</p><p>Once cooked, remove from the heat and keep covered until serving</p>",
            "order": 5,
            "image": "/images/instructions/kerala-egg-curry-with-coriander-rice-and-poppadoms/step-5.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Add your <strong>tomato paste</strong>, <strong>kashmiri-style chilli paste</strong>, <strong>curry powder</strong>,<strong> ginger & garlic paste</strong>, <strong>crushed cardamom </strong>and <strong>bay leaf[ves] </strong>with 1 tsp <span class=\"text-purple\">[1 1/2 tsp] </span><span class=\"text-danger\">[2 tsp] </span><strong>sugar</strong> and cook for 1-2 min or until fragrant</p><p>Once fragrant, add your <strong>cultured coconut </strong>with 200ml <span class=\"text-purple\">[250ml]</span> <span class=\"text-danger\">[350ml]</span> <strong>boiled water </strong>and cook for 5-6 min or until slightly thickened</p>",
            "order": 6,
            "image": "/images/instructions/kerala-egg-curry-with-coriander-rice-and-poppadoms/step-6.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Peel the <strong>cooled egg[s]</strong></p><p>Add the <strong>peeled eggs </strong>and the <strong>remaining garam masala </strong>to the pan and cook for 2 min or until warmed through \u2013 this is your <strong>Kerala egg curry</strong></p>",
            "order": 7,
            "image": "/images/instructions/kerala-egg-curry-with-coriander-rice-and-poppadoms/step-7.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Stir your <strong>chopped coriander</strong> through your cooked rice \u2013 this is your <strong>coriander rice</strong></p><p>Serve the <strong>Kerala egg curry</strong> with the <strong>coriander rice </strong>to the side and garnish with your<strong> crispy onions </strong>and the <strong>masala mustard butter</strong></p><p>Serve with your <strong>lime & coriander mini poppadoms </strong>and<strong> mint & coriander chutney</strong></p><p>Enjoy!</p>",
            "order": 8
        }
    ],
